eadings><font color=#A0B0E0>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#000000 class=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utayleondm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TayleonDM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 7:56:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> My guild is geting ready to start working on these guys regularly. We have done Vind, Zland and figured these were the next logical step. Anyone have any information that can help us on our way? Looking for mostly specs on these guys as well as any little tricks of the trade you can offer. =)<br><br>Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzyke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 8:06:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> Kland's AE is 400 dmg unresistable and sucks. Sont procs an AE dispell on his target. in addition to stripping buffs off your Mt at an alarming rate (4 at a time) Sont is often in the AE of his own dispell, and will dispell resist debuffs and Slow on him. Generally the Dispell won't hit anymore at the back of the dragon ( assume the tank is at the front =P). Sont's normal AE is FR obviously. Both have a weak fear AE.<br>The key to both of these is just how fast can you dish out damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uapollohades.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apollohades</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 8:33:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> If you can do Zland, you can do Kland really.<br><br>As far as Sont, just don't get him stuck on those damned statues as you will sometimes find other dragons suddenly hitting you from beneath the world.<br><br>As said by the previous poster, just do alot of damage quickly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unegilwintersfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Negil Wintersfury</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 12:29:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> We do them all fairly regularly, we don't use a ch chain on either, so perhaps save yourself some tries with regard to that, other than that HP/AC setup for Kland...Resist/HP set up for Sonta, Sonta has fewer hps the AE hits harder when it lands but is resistable, and yes kill'em fast.  Dragonbane doesn't work on either.<br><br>Cheers!<br><br>Neg <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utayleondm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TayleonDM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 12:46:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> Cool. Thanks.<br><br>So do people generally use, CH Rots on them or spread out the healers? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 12:47:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> so kland's fear is same as sontalak? i remember trying kland a long time ago and his fear was strong like kunark dragons.<br><br>as for heals, the fear and stuff can fuxor CH order and they have so few HP's that patch heals seem to work best. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usendailia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sendailia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 1:08:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> pretty sure the fear break down is...<br><br>sonta &lt;&lt; zland &lt; kland<br><br>Kland has the strongest fear, though not quite as strong as kunark dragons.  It does wonders for destroying a well timed cheal line, which is one of the reasons many guilds don't use them on him anylonger. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utaxxclandestine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taxx Clandestine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 2:01:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> What really helps is to have 2-3 bards with the new AE resist song.  With normal buffs and the song playing you should have no problem resisting the fear.  Sont's fear can be resisted naked =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utuxygnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TuxyGnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 10:21:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> Any post patch changes to these mobs?<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udagnyblazestorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dagny Blazestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 11:00:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> No one would know because the servers haven't been up long enough for them to spawn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubraylespellbreaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brayle Spellbreaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 12:55:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> Breakdown should be Sont &gt; Kland &gt;&gt; Zland <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udagnyblazestorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dagny Blazestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:37:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> He was talking about fear strength Brayle, not over all mob strength. I think that was right on target. I don't think I've ever been feared by Sont, I know Klandi will fear you for a short period of time but it won't last long. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umilt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milt</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:19:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sont and Kland</span><hr size=1> Is Klandicar easier or harder than Dozekar? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufflewddurfflam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fflewddur Fflam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 5:26:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> Klandicar and Sontalak are significantly harder than Dozekar.  <br><br>-FF <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urobbtherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>robb the rogue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 1:38:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> I am Mario.<br><br>I like to jump around, and would lead a fairly serene and aimless existence if it weren't for my friends always getting into trouble. I love to help out, even when it puts me at risk. I seem to make friends with people who just can't stay out of trouble.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarthunk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karthunk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 3:05:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;Klandicar and Sontalak are significantly harder than Dozekar.&lt;&lt;<br><br>Erm? Kland and Sont don't have 250khp and quad for 900. You know that ~400 dmg AE that strips a buff (that can't be resisted...)? With Dozekar you have to deal with it 2.5 times longer and it's easier? You can have everyone just rush Kland or Sont and win..you just blindly rush Dozer and you will be doing a CR. Hell we don't even use a chain for Sont or Kland. We just all rush and attack and lose like 4 people in the choas.<br><br>In short 250khp dragon &gt;&gt;&gt; then a dragon with less then 100khps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    . <br><br>I really love how people make fun of Dozer when he could easily go head to head with almost any one of the dragons in North and stand a good chance of winning.<br><br>Karthunk.....<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarthunk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karthunk</A> at: 3/18/02 3:09:54 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelessarcq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElessarCQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 3:11:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Spellshield works wonders for Kland/Sont, use it.  I generally used a CH order on the MT for them, tho rarely do you require it for very long if your dmg output is high enough.  Pally for each group works wonders as well if you manage to actually have some AE troubles later in the fight.  Their fears btw are nonfactors, nothing to worry about there.<br><br>And definitely Sont &gt; Kland &gt; Zland<br><br>Taliesn Soprano<br>Guildleader of Fallen Legacy<br>Lanys T'Vyl <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelessarcq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElessarCQ</A> at: 3/18/02 3:11:39 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udatalore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Datalore </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 3:12:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Dozekar is not "easy", he's just different. He can be done with fewer people who know and execute the strategy correctly, but that doesn't make him easier.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucordan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cordan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 3:40:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Imho (from the point of view of an melee heavy raiding guild) the progress line should be :<br><br>Zlandicar - Klandicar - Sontalak. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umerileafcatwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MerileafCatwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 5:29:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9828.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Doze is indeed easier for a lot of reasons. His melee damage is predictable. Slowed, 1 cleric can keep a MT alive against Doze. He also has a single dispell, 